this weekend was crazy. lets start with the stupid GRE class. so for the verbal and essay part of the GRE the classes were split up. last satruday we focused on the stories and senetence completion. this past saturday we were suppose to go over our essays and do analogies. the same guy was teaching both saturdays. last saturday i was the first one there and everyone shoed up like 10 minutes late. this past saturday everyone showed up 20 mintues late. so he was already mad that again everyone was late. then he asked the class if we knew the meaning of this one word. fof course no one knew it so we all stayed quiet. this one girl had made notcards of words that were in the book they gave us. so i asked her if that word was in her notecards. i guess other people were talking because the man got all mad and said that we didnt acknowledge he was there. so he steps out of the room and starts bitching about the entire class to the coordinator that was there. he comes in to the room and hands out examples gives us the answers, hands back our essays and tells us to leave. 
so at least we got out early. we all thought the whole thing was funny. 
annyways. i went back to my sisters and was bored out of my mind. so my old roomate calls me up and says that several people are going to have dinner so i decide to drive down to galveston and go. thats how bored i was. i then went fishing with my sister, her husband, and some of their friends. so that was fun. i caught 3 small fish. i was so happy.

later we went to this girls hotel to eat. it was fun and i was talking to these two guys about kaplan. they strongly recommended it. but they said that you have to use ALL of their resources. you cant just go to class and expect to do well. i asked them what they got and one of them got a 35 and the other a 36. yeah i was in shock because they were so not cocky about it at all. and they are really cool. not like that guy brice who expected everyone to kiss his ass because of what he got. one of them was saying that his montor at kaplan had suggested that he take a worst case scenerio mcat prep test. so he agreed. he said that his mentor and him went to a bar, got wasted, and woke up extra early to take the test. and do u want to know what he got? a 30!! i wish i got that now.

for the lab that i work for every visiting scientist or student has to sign in and out of the lab every day. just another security thing that the government requires after 9/11 for every selective agent lab. and my mentor was telling me about this act that had been passed after 9/11 stating that anyone from iran, iraq, afganistan, pakistan, and other countries in the middle east can not work in a US lab that works with selective agents. basically anything that can be used for bioterrorism. i think that kind of sucks. do be denied something because of ur race. i guess a small group of people can ruin it for the rest.

ok. for the past three days i've been taking the shuttle bus from the hotel to UTMB that leaves at 7:30 and gets to school at 8. the only problem is that i dont have to be in lab 'till 9. but when i brought my car it was a bitch to find parking. so i figured if i have to come early anyways to find parking might as well take the stupid shuttle. so know im here at the library trying to stay awake until 9 comes around. im just waiting for the day to be over because im going to my sisters for the weekend. hopefully i get to go to the mall, because good ol' galveston doesnt have one. 
yesterday i went to one of the professor's house that is in charge of the program. you know the one that looks like dr. wild. anyways, he has a beautiful house. its right on this lake. so several students were attempting to kayak. only one student fell into the water. good times. 
well, im going to try and stay awake for the next half our or so before i go to lab, its going to be a long day.

today i decided to drive over tu UTMB instead of taking the shuttle becuase i had to be in  later than the past two days. so after 30 minutes of looking for somehwere to park, i jusst ended up parking in a public garage because there was no student parking left. other than that though, i've been having a good day. my mentor is really nice, but it sucks that he has to leave for like three weeks next week. so im going to be switched to someone else. but he has a good reason for leaving, he's getting married. anyways, i dont know if i mentioned yesterday that the building i work in is crazzy. what i mean is that before u can go in u need to get through police and even then, u need a special chip in ur id to so that a door can open. in every single exit and entrance u need to swipe ur id so that the door can open. and in a hallway that has several doors, one has to be completely closed before the other can open. they said that after 9/11 it got crazy like that.

so today because i need someone to open the door everywhere, its kind of embarrasing to ask my male mentor to come escort me to the bathroom, wait for me, and escort me back. so during lunch i was practically peeing in my pants. so that was intersting.

well, im gonna head on over to lab and we'll see what other adventures await.

im just going to head back to my room and sleep because im so tired.

well, i got to galveston yesterday at like 12 in the afternoon because i wanted to be the first to check in to my room. jesenia had told me that there are three people in a one bedrooom condo and that there were two bunkbeds in the hall. so ofcourse i wanted the room. unfortunately check in werent until 3. so i had to wait with my sister and we decided to go eat. by the time i arrived to check in there were two girls infront of me in line. i thought to my self that it would be funny if one of them was my roomate. after the i got my key i noticed that the gilrs still had to get their lugage before going into the room. i found my room and settled into the bedroom. yay lucky me. literally a second later the gilr that was infront of me in line walks in. so had it not been for her luggage i would have been stuck with the bunk beds. the girl that was in back of me also happened to be my roomate. she was all pissed of about the living situation but tough shit. i GOT the room.  
overall one of my roomates is really nice and the other one is kind of mean beacuse she has literally said like two words to us. but oh well. 
yesterday we also had a cook out for all thoise in the program and i swear one of the professors in charge reminded me of dr. wild. only the funny thing was that he was wearing the tiniest shorts i had ever seen. i wouldnt even wear them. it was so funny.
today we had what had to be the longest orientation of my life. i was falling asleep. im just glad its over. 
we'll see how this summer turns out to be. luckily my sister is only like 30 minutes away from here and i get to visit often if i get too bored.
